s, das sich sprachlich in Form von Geschichten ausdrücken lässt. Erstmals findet der Leser in diesem Buch eine sowohl historische als auch systematische Einführung in die Emotionsforschung.  a"Emotions such as fear, shame, distrust are such an integral part of human existence that it is difficult to imagine what a human life would be like without them." What are emotions? How do we recognize them in ourselves and in others? In this book, Christiane Voss develops a theory of "narrative emotions". In her view, emotions are always based on a common structure, they are registered in a narrative and representational context of meaning. Voss provides both a historical and systematic introduction to this field.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aErzählforschung. 4aGefühl. 4aGefühlspsychologie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aStruktur. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH0 cprintz978311017943940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089626840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110896268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110896268/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014